bio:
🏡 takes time and ❤️
Currently renovating our mid-century modern home on a budget.
Sharing my tips and tricks along the way!

social_posts.post_text: I cannot believe how far we’ve come in our kitchen! It may not be completely done but that isn’t stopping me from decking the halls! The next big project is our window and door install and then we will tackle the flooring!

I found these adorable houses from the dollar section @target and I removed the bottoms of them to make them into an advent calendar! Each day my kids find a special little gift hidden under one and then I put a battery operated tea light under it. By the time Christmas arrives all the houses will be lit up ✨ Do you do an advent?! It’s one of my favorite traditions!

I used one of my favorite methods to transform our dining table. I combine chalk paint and wax to create the look of a wood finish without the hassle of sanding and staining. You can even use this method on items that are not made out of wood! It’s a total game changer! Check out my highlights to see the whole process…
#diyhomedecor #diyhomedecorating #diyhack #homestyle #woodtables #diningroom #diningroomdecor
This may be my favorite nook in our house! Our “magic” hidden pantry behind our main kitchen wall, it’s come a long way! What’s your favorite part?!

The sun was out today and it motivated me to get some herbs for our kitchen! Now let’s hope I can keep them alive! I love that our new kitchen layout lets in so much light. Having a window above our sink was a dream of mine and I’m so glad we made it happen! Swipe over to see the before of our kitchen.

I took a much needed break from instagram for the summer to spend time with family and refocus. After 2 years of non stop house renovations it was great to just enjoy our home but I did have time for a few projects 😉 can you spot the changes since I last shared?

I loved the painted beams in my house but I wanted to add a little warmth and depth! Unfortunately, I couldn’t just sand and stain them because lead paint had been detected on their surface. I got creative and covered them in peel and stick faux wood wallpaper 🙌 I couldn’t be happier with the outcome! What do you think?! “Wood” you try this in your home?! (Sorry for the pun I couldn’t help myself 😂)

Just because you’re on a budget doesn’t mean you have to sacrifice style!These barstools were $60 a piece 😱 I spray painted them to elevate the look! Even new items can be reimagined to fit your needs!
I love getting creative with secondhand finds! Just a little paint and some rub and buff and this thrifted lamp has new life! Follow along for more budget friendly home decor ideas.

1. Add wood elements! I used faux wood wallpaper to cover my beams and I painted the trim around my mural in the same tone. Wood adds depth and texture to any space. Don’t want to use wallpaper? Try adding other wood accents in your space!
2. Lighting! Lamps are a great way to cozy up any room! I gave my thrifted lamps a little makeover by painting them a warm red color to match my curtains. The soft glow of a lamp can instantly change your mood ✨
3. Play with different patterns! I decided to add more pattern in this space by choosing a rug with a diamond pattern. Don’t be afraid to mix patterns. Patterns can create interest and create a layered look! 
4. Plants! Mine just happen to be faux because I have a black thumb 😬 but I don’t think any room is complete without plants if some kind (real or faux)
Follow along for more tips! @slo.gathered.home 

#loveyourhome #woodbeams #diyhomedecorating #homelove #fallhomedecor #homedecor

I feel in love with the look of marble countertops and despite many hours of searching I couldn’t find an alternative that I loved as much as the real thing. So I found a slab I could actually afford. It has some cosmetic flaws (a superficial crack) but it’s almost impossible to see and it doesn’t affect the functionality of the countertop at all! Perfection is overrated right 😉 Also, I opted to use a cheaper slab (white quartz) for the perimeter of our kitchen to save even more and I actually love the contrast of the marble next to the quartz! What do you think of marble? Worth the splurge?
#marblecountertops #marblebacksplash #kitchenremodelingideas #kitchendesign #kitchendaily #interiordesign #kitchensofinsta

I’m all about easy and affordable Halloween decor!
1. Buy yourself some spooky shaped cutouts (or cut them out yourself)
2. Tape them to the inside of a light fixture or lamp shade
3. Turn on the light and boom instant Halloween magic!
#halloweendecorating #easyhalloweendecor #spookydecor #bathroomdesign

Peel and stick contact paper from Amazon has become my newest obsession. It started with my beams; I wanted a wood look but I couldn’t sand down and stain them so I ordered faux wood contact paper on a whim and what do you know? I loved it! Then I tried this faux rattan contact paper on my cabinet. Now no surface is safe, just kidding…maybe 😬 I have the whole process saved in my highlights if you’re interested (including links to the contact paper I used) but I must warn you it can become addicting! 
#diyhomeimprovements #amazonhomehacks #ceilingbeams #peelandstickwallpaper #mycurrenthomeview #ourspaceourplace #furnitureflips #easydiydecor #brepurposed #cljsquad #cljtransformations

Even though our fireplace is in the center of our home, we’ve spent the last couple of years ignoring it 😬 Adding a mantel and painting the bench has brought it back to life! Next up, I will do a treatment on the stone to soften it a bit, so stay tuned for that! All the details of how we built the mantel and how I painted it to look like stained wood can be found in my highlights. 
#christmasmantel #mantel #stonefireplace #fireplacemakeover #livingroomidea #homebeforeandafter

I can’t believe I waited so long to tackle this project! I loved the look of over-grouted stone but the amount of work it takes had me intimidated. Instead I opted to paint my grout with limestone paint here’s the details…
1. I used 1 quart (and I still have 1/2 of a quart left that I plan on using on the other side of our double-sided fireplace) of Romabio classic limewash paint in the color “riposo beige”
2. I diluted it with half parts water to paint ratio 
3. I used a spray bottle to dampen first 
4. Then I used a regular paint brush to paint the “grout” lines all around my stone

What do you think? Should I do a slight wash of the paint over the stone too? Let me know your thoughts and if you have any questions leave them in the comments. 

#stonefireplace #stonefireplaces #stonefireplacemakeover #overgroutedstone #fireplacemakeover #easydiys #budgetdiy #cljsquad #cljtransformations

Merry Christmas to me! My double sided fireplace is done 🙌 while I did lose a bet with my husband (I originally said I was going to wait until after Christmas to tackle this project but I have zero self control 😂) it was 100 percent worth it! I feel like this is how this fireplace was meant to look! And the best part is it was so easy! It cost me less than $40 to complete this project and only a little time. What do you think of the final results? 
#stonefireplace #fireplacemakeover #limewash #budgetdiy #diyhomerenovation #cljsquad #currenthomeview #smmakelifebeautiful

My three favorite DIYs this year all had something in common, they were affordable and attainable! It is my goal to keep sharing these kinds of DIYs next year along with more design tips and tricks to make your house into a home you love! Join me and follow along! I’m sharing more details of my favorite DIYs of 2023 below, which one was your favorite?

1. Pantry Reno: We used a combination of in stock cabinets from Lowe’s and cabinets we bought on Amazon to create storage in our pantry. I painted a piece of MDF to look like soapstone for the countertop and we used peel and stick floor tiles for flooring! 

2. Beams: I covered the beams in my house with peel and stick faux wood wallpaper that I found on Amazon. This was so easy and gave me the look I wanted without having to sand down and stain our beams which had previously been exposed to lead paint. 

3. Fireplace: I painted limewash on the mortar lines of my fireplace to soften and lighten it! It was so easy and transformative! 
#diyhomerenovation #bestof2023 #easydiys #budgetdiy

The number one comment I get when I share DIYs is “I wish I could be as brave as you are to try new things” Guess what?! You can! Here’s my secret…
I’m scared too 😬 Every single time I try something new! But here’s what I do to conquer my fear. It might seem counterintuitive but I ask myself, “what’s the worst thing that can happen?” I go down the path of what would happen if I fail and I create a plan to deal with the possibility of failure. This actually gives me the freedom to make mistakes and when you feel that freedom it allows your creativity to thrive! So here’s to making 2024 the year that curiosity wins, let’s create more together 🙌 What projects do you have planned for this year?
#creativediy #homehack #diyhouseprojects #diyhomerenovation #diylandscaping #smmakelifebeautiful #beckiowensfeature

My daughter and I decided to transform an old desk into a vanity for her room. She came up with the plan and was a part of every step of the makeover, I was excited to impart all of my furniture flipping wisdom to her! While I did get the opportunity to teach her a lot, the memories we made together were far more valuable than anything she learned! #furnitureflips #diyvanity #teengirlroom #girlroomideas #diytogether #vanityinspo
